Document Title: Engineering Circular – Drawing Revision for Viaduct Expansion Joint
Circular No.: ENG-CIRC/2025/017
Date: 09 September 2025
Issued By: Chief Engineer (Civil Works)

This circular serves to formally notify all contractors and site engineers about the revision of drawing DWG/CE/2025/017 concerning viaduct expansion joints between spans 23–26 of the Kakkanad Extension.

Key Changes Introduced:

- Replacement of 60 mm neoprene pad with 75 mm reinforced elastomeric bearing.

- Modified detailing of reinforcement mesh to reduce vibration resonance.

- Addition of stainless-steel cover plate to enhance durability under saline coastal conditions.

- Updated CAD drawing uploaded to SharePoint (Civil/Viaduct/2025).

Implementation Guidelines:

- Contractors must discontinue use of older versions effective immediately.

- Revised specifications must be incorporated into ongoing site work without exception.

- Resident Engineers are required to cross-verify compliance during daily inspections.

- Non-compliance will result in penalties as per contractual obligations.

Circulation & Acknowledgement:

- Hard copies of revised blueprint dispatched to site offices on 08 September.

- Digital version available under “Latest Drawings” repository.

- All queries regarding this circular to be addressed to Structural Engineering Division within 7 working days.

Follow-up Actions:

- Compliance confirmation to be submitted during Monthly Review Meeting scheduled for 30 September 2025.

- A joint audit with Quality Assurance team will be conducted in October to verify adherence.

This circular supersedes all prior communications on the subject, ensuring structural integrity and safety of the viaduct under expansion conditions.